PSKeyword

public PSKeyword(String label,
                 String description,
                 String value)
Create a new keyword for the specified parameters with an empty choice list.

Parameters:
label - the display label for the new keyword, not null or empty.
description - a description for the new keyword, may be null or empty.
value - the value for the new keyword, not null. This value will be used as the type for all choices.
Method Detail

createKeyword

public PSKeyword createKeyword(IPSGuid id,
                               PSKeywordChoice choice)
Create a new keyword for the supplied id and choice. This is needed because keywords and choices are stored in the same table and just interpret the content differently.

Parameters:
id - the guid of the keyword, not null.
choice - the choice for which to create a keyword, not null.
Returns:
the new created keyword for the supplied parameters, never null.

getKeywordType

public String getKeywordType()
Get the keyword type. For keywords, this value will be equivalent to KEYWORD_TYPE. For keyword choices, this value will be equivalent to the value of the parent keyword.

Returns:
the keyword type, never null or empty.
